### Git Push Blocker:
The repository has 3 new local commits ready to push, but cannot push due to authentication failure:
```
fatal: could not read Username for 'https://github.com': No such device or address
```

### Resolution Required (Manual):
The user needs to authenticate GitHub access using one of these methods:

**Option 1 - GitHub CLI (recommended):**
```bash
gh auth login
git push -u origin master
```

**Option 2 - Git credential helper:**
```bash
git config credential.helper store
git push -u origin master
```

**Option 3 - Switch to SSH:**
```bash
git remote set-url origin git@github.com:cletcher/chaprola-fitlog.git
git push -u origin master
```

All development work is complete. The blocker is documented in `inbox/QUESTIONS.md`.
